  "signature": "ed25519:b2d4e6f1a3c5e7d9b1f3a5c7e9d1b3f5a7c9e1d3b5f7a9c1e3d5b7f9a1c3e5d7",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-level3-openfast-version-control-ci",
      "rationale": "OpenFAST v3.4.1 is maintained under NREL's GitHub repository with continuous integration (CI) pipelines executing regression tests on each pull request. Version control history, release notes, and issue tracking are publicly accessible. The required Gradation 3 level reflects the certification-adjacent nature of the analysis; the achieved level is supported by documented CI pass records and the published OpenFAST Software Quality Assurance Plan (NREL/TP-5000-XXXXX)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/ncv-level3-method-of-manufactured-solutions",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) verification has been applied to the BeamDyn structural module and the AeroDyn15 aerodynamics module. Convergence rates match theoretical expectations (second-order in time, fourth-order in space for BeamDyn). Results are documented in NREL Technical Reports and peer-reviewed publications. Gradation 3 is required because the DEL predictions directly feed certification calculations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/disc-error-level2-grid-convergence-index",
      "rationale": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) analysis was performed across three time-step sizes (dt = 0.0125 s, 0.025 s, 0.05 s) and three BeamDyn element counts (5, 10, 20 elements per blade). The GCI for blade root flapwise moment is below 0.8% at the production time-step of 0.025 s with 10 elements. This exceeds the Gradation 2 threshold and achieves Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/nse-level2-residual-tolerance-monitoring",
      "rationale": "OpenFAST's tight-coupling Newton-Raphson solver is configured with a residual tolerance of 1e-6 for all coupled degrees of freedom. Solver convergence logs for all 72 DLC 1.1 seeds confirm no divergence events and residuals consistently below tolerance within three iterations. Gradation 2 is commensurate with the maturity of the solver and the non-safety-critical nature of the solver error factor relative to model-form uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Use error is assessed at Gradation 3 because the OpenFAST model configuration for the IEA 15-MW reference turbine has been independently reviewed by three subject-matter experts with combined experience exceeding 45 years in aeroelastic simulation of large offshore wind turbines. The review encompassed blade structural property tables, aerodynamic coefficient lookup tables (AeroDyn15 polar files), tower and drivetrain properties, and controller gain-scheduling parameters. A formal review checklist based on IEC 61400-13 and the IEA Wind Task 37 reference turbine definition document was completed and archived in the project configuration management system (CMR-2024-0047). Discrepancies identified during review — including an initial 2% error in the blade chord distribution at the 85% span station and an incorrect torsional stiffness coefficient at the blade root — were corrected prior to production runs, and re-review confirmed resolution. The simulation execution environment is containerised (Docker image sha256:d4e5f6...) to eliminate operator-induced environment variability across compute nodes. All production run scripts are version-controlled and peer-reviewed before execution. These controls collectively satisfy the Gradation 3 requirements as described in NASA-STD-7009B Table 4, which calls for independent expert review of model inputs and execution procedures, documented corrective action for identified errors, and reproducible execution environments. The assessment team considers this factor fully substantiated; detailed evidence is catalogued in the project credibility evidence dossier (CED-IEA15MW-DLC11-Rev2, Section 4.3)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-level3-physics-fidelity-review",
      "rationale": "OpenFAST couples geometrically exact beam theory (BeamDyn) with lifting-line aerodynamics including dynamic stall (DBEMT), wake induction (free-vortex wake via OLAF), and turbulent inflow (TurbSim Kaimal spectrum). This physics fidelity is appropriate for DLC 1.1 fatigue loads. Model form uncertainty is bounded by the code-to-code comparison against HAWC2 and Bladed (validation result VR-003), showing DEL agreement within ±5% across all wind speed bins."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-level3-uncertainty-quantification",
      "rationale": "Blade structural properties are derived from the IEA 15-MW public definition with supplementary finite-element cross-sectional analysis (BECAS). Aerodynamic polars are generated by XFoil with stall-delay corrections. Uncertainty in input parameters has been characterised qualitatively but a full probabilistic sensitivity analysis has not been completed; achievedLevel is therefore 2. A sensitivity study on key inputs (chord, twist, EI distribution) is planned for the next assessment cycle."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-level2-measurement-traceability",
      "rationale": "Strain gauge measurements at the blade root were collected during a 12-month field campaign on a prototype IEA 15-MW-class turbine. Six calibrated strain gauge bridges were installed per IEC 61400-13, with NIST-traceable calibration certificates. A total of 4,320 ten-minute records were collected across wind speed bins 4–24 m/s, providing statistically robust sample sizes (n > 200 per bin) for comparison. This exceeds the Gradation 2 requirement and achieves Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level2-met-mast-characterisation",
      "rationale": "Meteorological mast data at hub height confirm that the site turbulence intensity is consistent with IEC 61400-1 Class B conditions assumed in the simulation. Wind shear exponent and veer statistics are documented. Gradation 2 is achieved; Gradation 3 would require additional lidar profiling to characterise the full rotor-swept inflow, which is not available for this campaign."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/eip-level2-parameter-matching-protocol",
      "rationale": "Simulation input parameters (mean wind speed, turbulence intensity, wind shear, air density) have been matched to measured site conditions for each 10-minute comparison record using the parameter-matching protocol described in IEC 61400-13 Annex F. Residual mismatches are quantified and fall within acceptable bounds for Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level3-del-validation-metric",
      "rationale": "Predicted DELs are compared against measured DELs using the validation metric V = (DEL_sim - DEL_meas) / DEL_meas across all wind speed bins. The 90th-percentile absolute error is 4.2%, within the ±8% acceptance band established for Gradation 3. Statistical significance of the comparison is confirmed by bootstrap confidence intervals (n=1000, 95% CI: [−2.1%, +6.3%])."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/rqoi-level3-qoi-traceability-matrix",
      "rationale": "The quantity of interest — blade root flapwise and edgewise DELs at the Wöhler exponent m=10 relevant to GFRP laminates — is directly traceable to the certification requirement via a QoI traceability matrix (QTM-IEA15MW-Rev1). The validation measurements capture the same physical quantity at the same location, ensuring full relevance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/rvac-level3-cou-validation-gap-analysis",
      "rationale": "The validation campaign was conducted on a prototype turbine of the same design class but at a site with lower mean wind speed than the target deployment site. A validation gap analysis (VGA-IEA15MW-2024) identifies this geographic extrapolation as the primary gap reducing the achieved level to Gradation 2. Extrapolation uncertainty is bounded by sensitivity runs across the target site wind climate envelope."
    }
  ],
